]},{"section":6,"text":"Since serum osmolality is normal but sodium is low, that suggests possible pseudohyponatremia, but his osmolality is normal here.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.068384,0.11659,0.12366,0.11756,0.10551,0.091704,0.085081,0.075405,0.065471,0.058596,0.050626,0.041407],"unified_progress":[0.064033,0.094629,0.10489,0.10802,0.10988,0.10123,0.10914,0.082184,0.071352,0.0619,0.052836,0.039917]},{"section":7,"text":"Wait, pseudohyponatremia would have a low sodium but high osmolality because of elevated solutes like triglycerides or proteins.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.058119,0.10315,0.11257,0.11206,0.10579,0.095954,0.091293,0.081973,0.072247,0.065477,0.056285,0.045075],"unified_progress":[0.0576,0.087134,0.1011,0.10612,0.1093,0.10403,0.10961,0.086735,0.075701,0.066129,0.055517,0.041023]},{"section":8,"text":"But here the osmolality is normal, so it's true hyponatremia.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.05732,0.10146,0.11093,0.10952,0.10258,0.092929,0.089369,0.08169,0.07362,0.067559,0.060193,0.052837],"unified_progress":[0.056591,0.085437,0.098063,0.10402,0.10698,0.10037,0.1074,0.086183,0.076851,0.068147,0.060548,0.04941]},{"section":9,"text":"Now, looking at the urine sodium and osmolality.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.057366,0.10024,0.10726,0.1055,0.10008,0.092869,0.089091,0.083084,0.076753,0.070409,0.063109,0.054235],"unified_progress":[0.0599,0.086186,0.097064,0.10286,0.10519,0.09944,0.10467,0.087044,0.078724,0.070302,0.061125,0.047488]},{"section":10,"text":"The urine sodium is 40, which is on the higher side, but the urine osmolality is 450, which is quite concentrated.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.055932,0.10429,0.11499,0.11195,0.10353,0.093641,0.089882,0.081846,0.073954,0.065536,0.058681,0.045766],"unified_progress":[0.050866,0.091437,0.10433,0.10876,0.11204,0.10275,0.11112,0.085262,0.075082,0.064037,0.054681,0.039637]},{"section":11,"text":"The urine osmolality is higher than the serum osmolality.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.052173,0.099471,0.11097,0.11077,0.10444,0.095558,0.091762,0.083247,0.076542,0.067453,0.059879,0.047734],"unified_progress":[0.056064,0.08764,0.10139,0.10699,0.11057,0.10307,0.1123,0.085682,0.076098,0.064322,0.054854,0.041024]},{"section":12,"text":"That's a key point.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.33638,0.059705,0.059244,0.066591,0.064635,0.064555,0.058289,0.06507,0.062828,0.058129,0.05968,0.044891],"unified_progress":[0.2248,0.086984,0.071683,0.068561,0.076966,0.075537,0.084881,0.078676,0.071448,0.058508,0.052739,0.049217]},{"section":13,"text":"In hyponatremia, we need to figure out the cause.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.067095,0.13598,0.070696,0.10942,0.10067,0.096576,0.086502,0.078773,0.072571,0.066478,0.060271,0.054968],"unified_progress":[0.074384,0.099116,0.069724,0.097668,0.096798,0.10008,0.091716,0.086907,0.081851,0.076853,0.068891,0.056011]},{"section":14,"text":"The classic approach is to look at urine osmolality and urine sodium in the context of volume status.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.048457,0.089822,0.10054,0.10225,0.10095,0.096067,0.093663,0.086802,0.080364,0.075734,0.066712,0.058643],"unified_progress":[0.051748,0.079427,0.092233,0.097943,0.10147,0.099791,0.097788,0.090579,0.085144,0.078979,0.068825,0.056074]},{"section":15,"text":"Since the patient is on amitriptyline, which is a tricyclic antidepressant, I should consider if the hyponatremia is drug-induced.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.053203,0.090089,0.093952,0.09644,0.097382,0.098207,0.093341,0.089256,0.081488,0.079441,0.068141,0.059059],"unified_progress":[0.079718,0.095058,0.092948,0.092866,0.092988,0.093198,0.090187,0.088097,0.080534,0.075176,0.06589,0.053339]},{"section":16,"text":"TCA's can cause the syndrome of inappropriate antidiuresis (SIADH), which is a common side effect.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034518,0.070486,0.085277,0.098052,0.10542,0.10607,0.10509,0.095662,0.085064,0.085076,0.068648,0.060634],"unified_progress":[0.041548,0.066209,0.094068,0.095535,0.10006,0.10872,0.10201,0.097049,0.089725,0.083472,0.068047,0.053561]},{"section":17,"text":"SIADH occurs when there's excessive ADH secretion leading to water retention, diluting sodium.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033922,0.070425,0.083328,0.093881,0.10108,0.1031,0.10418,0.097417,0.089122,0.087592,0.072978,0.062969],"unified_progress":[0.050124,0.064671,0.081762,0.091347,0.097145,0.10372,0.10074,0.097958,0.092901,0.086564,0.074257,0.05881]},{"section":18,"text":"In SIADH, the serum osmolality is low-normal (since the body retains water), but here the serum osmolality is 260, which is actually in the lower end of normal (normal is around 280-290).","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.046758,0.087562,0.097803,0.10033,0.098835,0.095189,0.095834,0.090368,0.083802,0.077007,0.069577,0.056935],"unified_progress":[0.053285,0.08227,0.095485,0.10064,0.10516,0.10012,0.10014,0.089815,0.083564,0.074482,0.064983,0.050059]},{"section":19,"text":"Wait, 260 is below normal.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042095,0.081154,0.094456,0.099004,0.10038,0.097327,0.097101,0.092337,0.086651,0.078833,0.072022,0.058639],"unified_progress":[0.072048,0.082932,0.092737,0.10107,0.1024,0.096593,0.10155,0.086993,0.079219,0.073926,0.062703,0.047833]},{"section":20,"text":"Wait, the normal serum osmolality is about 280-295 mOsm/kg.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.051705,0.089297,0.097661,0.10046,0.099582,0.094824,0.094405,0.08867,0.081578,0.075833,0.068085,0.057904],"unified_progress":[0.063841,0.082907,0.095445,0.10169,0.10513,0.10004,0.10385,0.08733,0.078564,0.07106,0.061527,0.048623]},{"section":21,"text":"So 260 is low.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.043857,0.083596,0.096388,0.10033,0.10049,0.09625,0.096555,0.090787,0.084737,0.077163,0.071023,0.058817],"unified_progress":[0.082173,0.083399,0.092156,0.098259,0.10137,0.095772,0.10097,0.085939,0.077207,0.070616,0.062034,0.050107]},{"section":22,"text":"That would fit with hyponatremia due to SIADH.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040284,0.075911,0.086723,0.093153,0.096454,0.095771,0.09693,0.092654,0.087622,0.083963,0.077337,0.073197],"unified_progress":[0.051835,0.068804,0.082587,0.08918,0.094052,0.096062,0.096846,0.091613,0.088726,0.085457,0.081447,0.073391]},{"section":23,"text":"The urine sodium would be high (since kidneys are excreting sodium but retaining water), and the urine osmolality would be high because the kidneys are concentrating urine due to ADH.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038456,0.076965,0.088658,0.095019,0.097711,0.097657,0.099074,0.094179,0.090465,0.0826,0.075575,0.063641],"unified_progress":[0.063583,0.072904,0.085689,0.092028,0.098039,0.097804,0.098611,0.091904,0.087889,0.080967,0.072194,0.058388]},{"section":24,"text":"Wait, in SIADH, the urine sodium is typically >20 mEq/L because the kidneys are trying to excrete the excess water, but retain sodium.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.044452,0.0799,0.088456,0.094734,0.097848,0.096976,0.098296,0.093451,0.087482,0.081982,0.073573,0.06285],"unified_progress":[0.065961,0.074944,0.088191,0.094686,0.099242,0.099417,0.099799,0.091346,0.084932,0.078043,0.068165,0.055275]},{"section":25,"text":"The urine osmolality is higher than plasma, which is the case here (450 vs 260).","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.045185,0.084349,0.09424,0.097572,0.097308,0.094942,0.095256,0.09024,0.086249,0.079068,0.072669,0.062922],"unified_progress":[0.052018,0.079522,0.092941,0.09947,0.10369,0.10029,0.10189,0.089608,0.084076,0.075191,0.066853,0.05445]},{"section":26,"text":"That's a classic finding in SIADH.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.038349,0.072357,0.08526,0.091451,0.094254,0.093186,0.093792,0.091051,0.088687,0.086561,0.080687,0.084365],"unified_progress":[0.047672,0.065985,0.078249,0.088859,0.09091,0.092776,0.092965,0.091164,0.089303,0.088374,0.086874,0.08687]},{"section":27,"text":"Other possibilities for hyponatremia: hypovolemic causes like diuretics (but he's on amitriptyline, not diuretics), or hypervolemic like heart failure, but his exam is normal.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03662,0.074301,0.084375,0.090645,0.095646,0.099694,0.099131,0.096745,0.091385,0.08825,0.078476,0.064731],"unified_progress":[0.05039,0.081843,0.087582,0.089959,0.09403,0.096693,0.095215,0.094742,0.090078,0.085991,0.075242,0.058237]},{"section":28,"text":"Euvolemic causes include SIADH, hypothyroidism, or adrenal insufficiency.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02994,0.066943,0.081934,0.092333,0.099354,0.10214,0.10374,0.099155,0.09281,0.089948,0.078021,0.063683],"unified_progress":[0.036775,0.068887,0.087576,0.094395,0.099547,0.10396,0.10207,0.09806,0.093011,0.087151,0.073437,0.055133]},{"section":29,"text":"Since he's on a medication known to cause SIADH, that's the most likely.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.03374,0.068468,0.079319,0.086273,0.092367,0.099822,0.096779,0.096092,0.092436,0.091275,0.083186,0.080243],"unified_progress":[0.072265,0.099721,0.088165,0.08505,0.083879,0.085911,0.082781,0.086283,0.082016,0.079143,0.078361,0.076425]},{"section":30,"text":"Hypothyroidism or adrenal insufficiency would have other signs, like low TSH or high ACTH, but the exam is normal.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030458,0.067238,0.081562,0.089415,0.094046,0.097217,0.10143,0.099203,0.096158,0.091952,0.085127,0.066194],"unified_progress":[0.044292,0.076051,0.087738,0.091834,0.09909,0.097818,0.09765,0.095101,0.091582,0.088611,0.07573,0.054502]},{"section":31,"text":"So the most likely is SIADH caused by amitriptyline.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025277,0.05269,0.063758,0.071897,0.079605,0.08613,0.090658,0.092889,0.095776,0.096866,0.10258,0.14187],"unified_progress":[0.031957,0.049875,0.057369,0.065394,0.069402,0.0785,0.080129,0.088103,0.093457,0.098651,0.12492,0.16225]},{"section":32,"text":"<answer> Syndrome of Inappropriate Antidiuretic Hormone Secretion (SIADH) </answer>","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033512,0.060751,0.066494,0.074027,0.08149,0.08719,0.092147,0.093448,0.094291,0.096767,0.0969,0.12298],"unified_progress":[0.036398,0.046562,0.057496,0.06528,0.072008,0.081771,0.08384,0.09266,0.097727,0.10157,0.11791,0.14678]}]}}